<Content>Nice We stayed at the Majestic for 3 nights during our honeymoon upon recommendation of a frequent traveler to Barcelona. The location is great, it's away from all the touristy places and is located in a very nice/quiet fashionable district. Shopping is very near to be found. The architecture on this street is amazing!!!! You are within 2 minutes walk to a couple of buildings designed by Gaudi. Barcelona is an amazing town, we absolutely loved it. The one hang up that I have about the Majestic is that while we were there during August 2003, there was construction happening on to the facade of the building therefore the front of the building had a huge advertisement on it. The front desk was very nice and sent up a bottle of champagne to our room, upon informing them that we don't drink, they sent up a plate full of fruit along with mineral water, a very nice gesture. This hotel was very nice and I would highly recommend it to anyone. 
